    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Two statements, one Assertion (A) and the other Reason (R) are given. Choose the correct option.</p>\n<p>Assertion: 2-aminoethanoic acid and p-aminobenzene sulphonic acid can exist as Zwitter ions while p-aminobenzoic acid cannot.</p>\n<p>Reason: When the acid group is a relatively strong proton donor and the $-\\mathrm{NH}_2$ group is sufficiently basic it can accept a $\\mathrm{H}^{+}$ion from the acid group to form the dipolar ion.</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Both A and R are correct and R is the correct explanation of A ."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " A is correct but R is wrong.\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " A is wrong but R is correct."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Both A and R are correct but R is not the correct explanation of A ."
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The correct choice is A.</p>\n<p>Explanation:</p>\n\n<p><p>2-Aminoethanoic acid (glycine) and p-aminobenzenesulfonic acid both have  </p>\n<p>– a strongly acidic group (–COOH in glycine, –SO₃H in the sulfonic acid)  </p>\n<p>– a basic –NH₂ group in the same molecule.  </p>\n<p>Because the acid group is strong enough to give up H⁺ and the –NH₂ is basic enough to accept it, they undergo intramolecular proton transfer and exist as zwitterions:  </p>\n<p>$$\\text{HOOC–CH₂–NH₂}\\;\\longrightarrow\\; ^{–}\\text{OOC–CH₂–NH₃}^{+} $$  </p>\n<p>$$\\text{H₂N–C₆H₄–SO₃H}\\;\\longrightarrow\\; ^{+}\\text{H₃N–C₆H₄–SO₃}^{–} $$  </p></p>\n<p><p>In p-aminobenzoic acid the –COOH is not acidic enough (pKa≈4.2) relative to the basicity of aniline-type –NH₂ (pKa of the conjugate acid ≈4.6), and the geometry (para-arrangement on the ring) doesn’t favor intramolecular transfer. So no stable internal salt is formed.</p></p>\n\n<p>Thus both the Assertion and the Reason are correct, and the Reason correctly explains the Assertion.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "comedk-2025-morning-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
