    "content": "<p>In a set of reactions, bromoethane yielded a final product 'S'.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lwqjc0ny/4ea5f770-e652-45fe-a081-e5d107c6f8b3/86a527e0-1d04-11ef-8341-29ca1435c2d9/file-1lwqjc0nz.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lwqjc0ny/4ea5f770-e652-45fe-a081-e5d107c6f8b3/86a527e0-1d04-11ef-8341-29ca1435c2d9/file-1lwqjc0nz.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"COMEDK 2024 Afternoon Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 10 English\"></p>\n<p>The compound 'S' should be</p>",
