  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Among the following compounds, the most acidic is :</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "3, 4-dinitrobenzoic acid\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Benzoic acid\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "4-methoxybenzoic acid\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "4-nitrobenzoic acid"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The acidity of a benzoic acid derivative is largely influenced by the substituents on the benzene ring. Electron-withdrawing groups stabilize the negative charge on the conjugate base (the carboxylate ion), thereby increasing the acidity, while electron-donating groups have the opposite effect.</p>\n<p>Here's a breakdown of the options:</p>\n\n<p>$$\\textbf{Benzoic Acid:}$$  </p>\n\n\n<p>This is the basic structure with no additional substituents, so its acidity is moderate.</p>\n\n\n<p>$$\\textbf{4-methoxybenzoic acid:}$$  </p>\n\n\n<p>The methoxy group ($$\\text{–OCH}_3$$) is an electron-donating group via resonance (+M effect), which destabilizes the carboxylate ion and decreases the acidity.</p>\n\n\n<p>$$\\textbf{4-nitrobenzoic acid:}$$  </p>\n\n\n<p>The nitro group ($$\\text{–NO}_2$$) is a strong electron-withdrawing group. When attached at the para position relative to the carboxyl group, it withdraws electrons through both the inductive (–I) and resonance (–M) effects, thereby increasing the acidity compared to benzoic acid.</p>\n\n\n<p>$$\\textbf{3,4-dinitrobenzoic acid:}$$  </p>\n\n\n<p>In this compound, there are two nitro groups. One is at the para position, contributing strong -I and -M effects, and the other at the meta position mainly contributes via strong -I effects. The combined effect of two nitro groups is greater stabilization of the carboxylate ion, making this compound considerably more acidic than the others.</p>\n\n<p>Thus, the most acidic compound among the given options is:</p>\n<p>$$\\textbf{Option A: 3,4-dinitrobenzoic acid.}$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "comedk-2024-afternoon-shift",
    "difficulty": null
  },
